---
layout: base.njk
permalink: /index.html
title: "Backyard Math | Free Landscaping, Garden & Outdoor Project Calculators"
description: "Free calculators for landscaping, gardening, patios, fire pits, fencing, gravel, mulch, concrete, and other outdoor projects."
---
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">DIY planning tools for real homeowners</p>
          <h1>Plan outdoor projects without guessing.</h1>
          <p class="hero-copy">
            Use simple calculators to estimate mulch, gravel, soil, pavers, concrete, retaining walls, and fire pit materials before you buy.
          </p>
          <a class="button" href="/calculators/concrete.html">Try the Concrete Calculator</a>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-card">
          <h2>Popular tools</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Concrete Calculator</li>
            <li>Gravel Calculator</li>
            <li>Raised Bed Soil Calculator</li>
            <li>Fire Pit Gravel Calculator</li>
            <li>Fence Cost Calculator</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="calculators" class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Homeowner calculators</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">Estimate materials for common landscaping, garden, fire pit, and hardscaping projects.</p>

        {% for group in categorizedCalculators %}
        <div class="category-section">
          <h3>{{ group.category }}</h3>
          <div class="card-grid category-grid">
          {% for calc in group.items %}
          <a class="tool-card" href="{{ calc.href }}">
            <span class="category-pill" data-category="{{ calc.category }}">{{ calc.category }}</span>
            <h3>{{ calc.title }}</h3>
            <p>{{ calc.description }}</p>
          </a>
          {% endfor %}
          </div>
        </div>
        {% endfor %}

      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="how-it-works" class="section muted">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h2>How it works</h2>
        <p>
          Enter your project measurements, choose your material depth or product size, and get a quick planning estimate.
          These tools use standard area and volume formulas, then add optional overage where homeowners commonly need extra material.
        </p>
        <p>
          For the most reliable estimate, use product dimensions and material weights from your local supplier whenever available.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
